{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a cross-module state-consistency rule (summary write path must consult stored per-dimension findings). Unit tests on summary composition alone can miss repository/service handoff bugs. Rejected Agentic/System because behavior text is about stored verdict data checks, not real model-output quality or external network/OS contracts.","test_description":"Create a round with persisted per-dimension findings including at least one FAIL, attempt to persist a PASS summary for that same round through the service/repository path, and assert the write is rejected with a policy error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure mode is data-source selection across modules (gate logic + storage). Unit-only checks can falsely pass if they never exercise real repository wiring. Rejected System/Agentic because no explicit requirement for real external contract checks or real model decision quality.","test_description":"Persist conflicting data (summary text says PASS, stored dimension finding includes FAIL), run stop-gate computation end-to-end in-process, and assert verdict is FAIL/blocked based on stored findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior couples authorization/flag validation with persistence of an audit artifact. That interaction is beyond single-function logic. Rejected System because behavior does not explicitly require validating an external API/logging contract via real boundary round-trip.","test_description":"Attempt manual override without flag and assert rejection; then repeat with explicit override flag and assert summary is accepted and an audit warning record is persisted with actor, round, and reason metadata.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the gate requires a review round identifier produced after the latest fix commit before PASS can be finalized.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Core risk is temporal/state linkage between fix metadata and review-round metadata across modules. In-process integration can catch stale-round acceptance bugs. Rejected System because the behavior text does not explicitly require real git subprocess/exit-code contract validation; commit chronology can be represented in persisted metadata for this check.","test_description":"Persist a latest-fix commit marker newer than the most recent review round id, attempt PASS finalization and assert blocked; then persist a new review round id tied to post-fix state and assert PASS can proceed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"If implementation derives commit state only via real git subprocess (not persisted metadata), upgrade to System.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.63,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"In the live review loop, PASS cannot finalize unless a fresh review-agent round runs on the updated diff.","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is orchestration correctness across an LLM-involved stage in a live loop. A stubbed agent can hide freshness/handoff failures tied to real agent execution timing and run identity. Rejected Workflow because behavior requires one fresh agentic round gate, not validating consistency across multiple model-dependent steps.","test_description":"Run the live loop on an updated diff, attempt PASS without executing a new real review-agent round and assert block; execute a real fresh review-agent round on that updated diff and assert gate now allows PASS subject to findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings in stored results, the outcome is escalation rather than PASS.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Decision depends on combining round-count policy with persisted finding severities; this is module interaction/state aggregation. Rejected Agentic because behavior explicitly keys off stored results, not evaluating model-output quality in real time.","test_description":"Persist state where max rounds is reached and unresolved MUST-FIX findings remain, run gate decision path, and assert outcome is escalation and PASS is denied.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"In a live multi-round review workflow, exhausted rounds with unresolved MUST-FIX findings still block PASS and emit escalation.","required_reality_check_level":"Workflow","justification":"Pass/fail depends on sequence-level behavior across multiple rounds in a live agent pipeline (state must remain consistent across steps until exhaustion). Unit/Integration can miss cross-round drift and terminal-state gating bugs. Rejected Agentic because this explicitly requires multi-round sequencing, not a single model-dependent step.","test_description":"Execute a real multi-round review workflow where MUST-FIX remains unresolved through round exhaustion; verify terminal outcome blocks PASS and emits escalation artifact/event at workflow end.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
